:::

## Blocky Admonitions

Create vibrant, high-impact admonitions with solid colored backgrounds:

```css
:root {
  --admonition-title-background-tint: 30%;
  --admonition-content-background-tint: 30%;
  --admonition-border-radius: 0;
  --admonition-border-width: 0;
  --admonition-accent-border-width: 4px;
}
```

::: style --admonition-title-background-tint: 30%; --admonition-content-background-tint: 30%; --admonition-border-radius: 0; --admonition-border-width: 0; --admonition-accent-border-width: 4px;

> [!info] Bold Styling
> This example demonstrates vibrant, high-impact styling using 30% background tints for both title and content, no border radius, no main borders, and a thick 4px accent border.

:::

## Subtle Admonitions

Minimal visual emphasis with subtle backgrounds and reduced opacity for discrete callouts:

```css
:root {
  --admonition-title-background-tint: 8%;
  --admonition-content-background-tint: 4%;
  --admonition-border-opacity: 50%;
  --admonition-border-width: 0;
  --admonition-accent-border-width: 3px;
  --surface-background: #1a1a1a;
  --text-color-primary: #e0e0e0;
}
```

::: style --admonition-title-background-tint: 8%; --admonition-content-background-tint: 4%; --admonition-border-opacity: 50%; --admonition-border-width: 0; --admonition-accent-border-width: 3px; --surface-background: #1a1a1a; --text-color-primary: #e0e0e0;

> [!important] Subtle Styling
> This example demonstrates minimal visual emphasis using reduced background tints (8% title, 4% content), lighter borders (50% opacity), no main border, a 3px accent border, and a dark color scheme. Perfect for discrete callouts that don't dominate the page.

:::

# Tips

**Leverage semantic types**: Choose admonition types based on semantic meaning (Note, Warning, Error) rather than desired visual appearance. This ensures proper communication for screen readers and other assistive technologies.

**Use spacing tokens**: Customize spacing through `--admonition-spacing` and `--admonition-padding` rather than overriding semantic tokens like `--content-spacing`, which affects the entire document.

**Prefer semantic integration**: Admonition spacing inherits from `--content-spacing` by default, providing automatic responsive behavior. Override only when specific adjustments are needed.

**Color customization made simple**: Change type-specific color tokens (e.g., `--admonition-warning-color`) to update icon, border, and background colors simultaneously. Dark mode variants are applied automatically.

**Icon customization**: Adjust icon size via `--admonition-icon-size` for visual hierarchy. Larger icons (1.5em+) work well for critical warnings, while smaller icons (1em) suit subtle notes.

**Collapsible for optional content**: Use collapsible admonitions (`is-folded` attribute) for supplementary information that readers may want to skip. Keep critical warnings always visible.

**Test dark mode**: When changing type-specific colors, set both the light and dark tokens (e.g., `--admonition-warning-color` and `--admonition-warning-color-dark`) to maintain intended contrast across color schemes.

**Avoid heavy nesting**: While admonitions support nesting, limit depth to 2-3 levels maximum for readability. Deep nesting can confuse readers and create visual clutter.

**Typography hierarchy**: Use `--admonition-title-font-size` and `--admonition-title-font-weight` to establish visual hierarchy. Important warnings benefit from bolder, larger titles.

**Mobile considerations**: Test admonitions on mobile devices to ensure touch targets for collapsible toggles are adequately sized and spacing remains readable at smaller screen widths.
